article.headline: Ark.-Little Rock 75, Denver 72
article.story: LITTLE ROCK, Ark. -- Matt Mouzy scored 24 points, making 8 of 10 from 3-point range, and Arkansas-Little Rock beat Denver 75-72 in overtime Thursday night. Mouzy made a pair of jumpers to start the overtime period, and after Denver came back to take a 72-71 lead, Daylon Guy and D'Andre Williams each made a pair of free throws for Arkansas-Little Rock. Solomon Bozeman had 15 points and Alex Garcia-Mendoza scored 14 for the Trojans (13-11, 5-4 Sun Belt). Chase Hallam led Denver (11-12, 7-2) with 22 points. Travis Hallam had 17. The Hallam brothers combined for eight 3-pointers for the Pioneers. Chase Hallam, off a pass from Travis, tied the game with a 3 as regulation time was running out.
